    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-07-20T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-07-20T04:00:00-05:00" n="453"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d453">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/3411: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Fuller</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-07-20T17:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1920—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 22—8:27 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Military train reached Peking July 20, 1 a.m. without difficulty, left there July
                    20, 11 a.m., telephone communication is restored. Military commandants have
                    decided to run one daily mail train. Ma Liang is now attacking Chihli forces
                    near Tehchow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fuller</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
